    'Jn 1:33': 'And I did not know him; but the one who sent me to baptize in water, that one said to me, "Upon whom you see the Spirit descending and remaining upon him, this is the one baptizing in [the] Holy Spirit."',
    'Jn 3:2': 'This man came to Jesus by night, and said to him, "Rabbi, we know that you have come from God [as] a teacher; for no one is able to do these signs which you do, unless God is with him."',
    'Jn 3:11': 'Truly, truly I say to you that what we know we speak and what we have seen we bear witness, and our witness you do not receive.',
    'Jn 4:22': 'You worship what you do not know; we worship what we know, because the salvation is from the Jews;',
    'Jn 5:19': 'Therefore Jesus answered and was saying to them, "Truly, truly I say to you, the Son is not able to do anything from himself unless he sees the Father doing something; for whatever that one does, these the Son also does likewise."',
    'Jn 5:30': 'I am not able to do anything from myself; just as I hear, I judge, and my judgment is righteous, because I do not seek my [own] will but the will of the one who sent me.',
    'Jn 5:32': 'Another it is who bears witness concerning me, and I know that the witness which he bears witness concerning me is true.',
    'Jn 5:44': 'How are you able to believe, receiving glory from one another, and the glory which is from the only God you do not seek?',
    'Jn 6:6': 'But this he was saying, testing him; for he himself knew what he was about to do.',
    'Jn 6:42': 'And they were saying, "Is this not Jesus the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? How does he now say that, \'I have come down from heaven\'?"',
    'Jn 7:7': 'The world is not able to hate you; but it hates me, because I bear witness concerning it that its works are evil.',
    'Jn 7:18': 'The one speaking from himself seeks his own glory; but the one seeking the glory of the one who sent him, this one is true and unrighteousness is not in him.',
    'Jn 7:27': 'But this one we know from where he is; but the Christ, whenever he comes, no one knows from where he is.',
    'Jn 7:28': 'Therefore Jesus, teaching in the temple, cried out and saying, "You both know me and know from where I am; and from myself I have not come, but the one who sent me is true, whom you do not know;',
    'Jn 7:34': 'You will seek me and you will not find [me], and where I am you are not able to come.',
    'Jn 7:36': 'What is this saying which he said: "You will seek me and you will not find [me], and where I am you are not able to come"?',
    'Jn 8:19': 'They were saying therefore to him, "Where is your father?" Jesus answered, "You know neither me nor my Father; if you had known me, you would have known my Father also."',
    'Jn 8:21': 'Therefore he said again to them, "I am going away and you will seek me, and in your sin you will die; where I am going you are not able to come."',
    'Jn 9:4': 'It is necessary [for] us to work the works of the one who sent me while it is day; night is coming when no one is able to work.',
    'Jn 9:12': 'And they said to him, "Where is that one?" He says, "I do not know."',
    'Jn 9:25': 'Therefore that one answered, "Whether he is a sinner I do not know; one [thing] I know — that being blind, now I see."',
    'Jn 9:29': 'We know that God has spoken to Moses, but this one we do not know from where he is.',
    'Jn 9:33': 'If this one were not from God, he would not be able to do anything.',
    'Jn 10:4': 'Whenever he casts out all his own, he goes before them, and the sheep follow him, because they know his voice;',
    'Jn 10:35': 'If those he called gods to whom the word of God came, and the scripture is not able to be loosed,',
    'Jn 11:37': 'But some of them said, "Was not this one, the [one] having opened the eyes of the blind man, able to do [something] in order that this one also might not die?"',
    'Jn 12:50': 'And I know that his commandment is eternal life. Therefore the things I speak — just as the Father has said to me, thus I speak.',
    'Jn 13:7': 'Jesus answered and said to him, "What I am doing you do not know now, but you will know after these things."',
    'Jn 13:17': 'If you know these things, you are blessed if you do them.',
    'Jn 14:4': 'And where I am going you know the way.',
    'Jn 14:7': 'If you have known me, you will also know my Father; and from now you know him and have seen him.',
    'Jn 14:17': 'the Spirit of truth, whom the world is not able to receive, because it does not behold him nor know [him]; but you know him, because he remains alongside you and will be in you.',
    'Jn 15:3': 'You are already clean on account of the word which I have spoken to you;',
    'Jn 15:15': 'I no longer call you slaves, because the slave does not know what his master does; but I have called you friends, because all that I heard from my Father I made known to you.',
    'Jn 15:21': 'But all these things they will do to you on account of my name, because they do not know the one who sent me.',
    'Jn 16:12': 'I still have many things to say to you, but you are not able to bear [them] now;',
    'Jn 19:35': 'And the one having seen has borne witness, and his witness is true, and that one knows that he speaks true things, in order that you also may believe.',
    'Jn 21:24': 'This is the disciple bearing witness concerning these things and the one having written these things, and we know that his witness is true.',
    'Ac 2:34': 'For David did not ascend into the heavens, but he himself says, "[The] Lord said to my Lord, \'Sit at my right [hand],\'',
