    'Mt 18:30': 'But he was not willing, but going away, he threw him into prison until he should pay back what is owed.',
    'Mt 19:13': 'Then children were brought to him in order that he might lay hands on them and pray; but the disciples rebuked them.',
    'Mt 19:14': 'But Jesus said, "Permit the children, and do not hinder them from coming to me; for of such is the kingdom of the heavens."',
    'Mt 19:15': 'And having laid hands on them, he went away from there.',
