    'Mt 19:27': 'Then Peter, answering, said to him, "Behold, we left all and followed you; what then will be for us?"',
    'Mt 20:4': 'And to those he said, "You also go into the vineyard, and whatever is right I will give you";',
    'Mt 20:14': 'Take what is yours and go; but I want to give to this last [one] as also to you;',
    'Mt 20:32': 'And Jesus, having stood, called them and said, "What do you want me to do for you?"',
    'Mt 21:4': 'But this has happened in order that what was spoken through the prophet might be fulfilled, saying:',
    'Mt 21:23': 'And when he had come into the temple, the chief priests and the elders of the people came to him while teaching, saying, "By what authority do you do these things? And who gave you this authority?"',
    'Mt 21:24': 'And Jesus, answering, said to them, "I will also ask you one word, which if you tell me, I also will tell you by what authority I do these things;',
    'Mt 21:27': 'And answering Jesus, they said, "We do not know." He himself also said to them, "Neither do I tell you by what authority I do these things."',
    'Mt 21:43': 'On account of this I tell you that the kingdom of God will be taken from you and given to a nation producing its fruits.',
    'Mt 22:21': 'They say to him, "Caesar\'s." Then he says to them, "Therefore render the things of Caesar to Caesar, and the things of God to God."',
    'Mt 22:22': 'And hearing, they marveled, and leaving him, they went away.',
